cells.text: See accompanying Consolidated Financial Statements. Significant events include the following:

cells.text: Four Rivers Transportation (“FRT”), a short-line railroad previously accounted for under the equity method, in conjunction with adoption of FASB

cells.text: Interpretation No. 46, “Consolidation of Variable Interest Entities.” Net equity earnings of FRT of approximately $4 million were included in other income in 2003.

cells.text: – CSX completed a corporate reorganization of Conrail that resulted in the direct ownership of certain Conrail assets by CSXT. This transaction was accounted

cells.text: for at fair value and resulted in a net gain of $16 million after tax, which is included in other income. (See Note 2. Investment In and Integrated Rail

cells.text: Operations with Conrail.)

cells.text: – In December 2004, CSX entered into a definitive agreement to sell its international terminals business for $1.142 billion in cash and other consideration.
cells.text_vi: - Vào tháng 12 năm 2004, CSX đã ký một thỏa thuận dứt khoát để bán doanh nghiệp Terminals quốc tế của mình với giá 1,142 tỷ đô la tiền mặt và xem xét khác.

cells.text: As a result, amounts related to this business are reported as discontinued operations for all periods presented.
cells.text_vi: Do đó, số lượng liên quan đến doanh nghiệp này được báo cáo là hoạt động đã ngừng hoạt động cho tất cả các giai đoạn được trình bày.

cells.text: Group for approximately $300 million. CSX Lines was subsequently renamed Horizon. A deferred pretax gain of approximately $127 million as a result of the

cells.text: received $59 million, which included $48 million for the purchase of its ownership interest in Horizon, $4 million of interest and a performance payment of $7 million.
